        <h2 class="Heading2"><a name="kanchor118"></a>Opening a port for a new component</h2>
        <p>You can open a new port for an additional <span class="VariablesProductName">DigitalEdge</span> component at any time.</p>
        <ol>
            <li value="1">Add the new component in <b>System Builder</b>.</li>
            <li value="2">Use the <b>Management Console</b> to specify a security rule and the port settings:
		<ol><li value="1">Select  <b>Security </b>&gt; [select a security group] &gt; <b>Add Security Rule</b>. The <b>Add New Security Rule</b> dialog box prompts for details.</li><li value="2">Select a <b>Protocol</b> from the drop-down menu (TCP, UDP, or ICMP).</li><li value="3">Enter a <b>Port Range</b> (one port number or a range of ports).</li><li value="4">Enter a communications <b>Source</b>. A source can be an IP address, a range of IP addresses, or another security group that can talk with the assigned process groups. </li><li value="5">Click <b>ADD</b>.</li></ol></li>
        </ol>
